+## WALLET-210 Partner Pilot Rehearsal
+
+Run this rehearsal in target staging before a 211 service partner pilot and
+after changes to verifier, storage, analytics, sharing, revocation, or audit
+configuration. Use synthetic pilot data and archive evidence references only.
+
+Preflight:
+
+```bash
+python -m wallet_interface.ops --validate-proof-contract --fail-on-error
+python -m wallet_interface.ops --validate-distance-proof-contract --fail-on-error
+python -m wallet_interface.ops --validate-production-readiness
+python scripts/run_wallet_release_checks.py --dry-run
+```
+
+The staging deployment must already have WALLET-170, WALLET-180, WALLET-190,
+and WALLET-200 evidence for the same API/UI build, storage topology, verifier
+backend, and analytics template set.
+
+Pilot demo sequence:
+
+1. Create or load a synthetic wallet and add a document through 211-AI
+   `#/uploads`. Confirm `record/add` appears in `#/audit` and encrypted storage
+   verification reports only ciphertext hashes and storage refs.
+2. Add a precise location with `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations`. Record
+   only the location record ID in the evidence ticket; do not paste latitude or
+   longitude into evidence.
+3. Have the partner request `record/analyze` access for the document with a
+   purpose such as `housing_navigation_intake`, then approve it from 211-AI
+   `#/recipient-access`. Confirm the active receipt shows the partner DID,
+   purpose, abilities, and receipt hash.
+4. As the partner, run a redacted analysis or summary from
+   `#/recipient-access`. Evidence must show derived or redacted output only.
+5. Create a `location_region` proof from 211-AI `#/proof-center`. The receipt
+   must be non-simulated in target staging and public inputs must exclude
+   `lat`, `lon`, witnesses, target coordinates, and credentials.
+6. Create consent from an approved analytics template, contribute only approved
+   derived fields, and run an approved aggregate count. Confirm released
+   aggregate metadata and privacy-budget spend are recorded without raw fields.
+7. Revoke the partner request or grant from `#/recipient-access`. Confirm
+   `GET /wallets/{wallet_id}/grant-receipts?status=revoked` lists the grant and
+   a post-revocation partner call fails.
+8. Open `#/audit` and `GET /wallets/{wallet_id}/audit`. The timeline must cover
+   document add, access request, approval, partner use, proof creation,
+   analytics consent, contribution, query, access revoke, and grant revoke.
+
+Stop the rehearsal and file a launch blocker if any artifact exposes plaintext
+document contents, contact details outside an explicitly granted decrypt flow,
+precise coordinates, proof witnesses, key material, bearer tokens, resolved
+secret values, or analytics fields outside the approved template.
+
+Local validation for this path:
+
+```bash
+pytest tests/test_wallet_interface_api.py tests/test_wallet_third_party_blackbox.py -q
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui run build
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui test -- tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts
+```
+
