+## 211 Service Partner Pilot Readiness
+
+Use this checklist for the final target-staging rehearsal before a 211 service
+partner pilot. It assumes WALLET-170 third-party sharing, WALLET-180 verifier
+cutover, WALLET-190 retention dry-run, and WALLET-200 analytics governance
+evidence have already been archived for the same staging deployment.
+
+Required pilot path:
+
+| Step | Surface | Evidence |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| Add user documents | 211-AI `#/uploads`, `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/documents`, or `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/documents/text` | Encrypted `record/add` audit event and storage status; no plaintext in logs or tickets. |
+| Add precise location | `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations` | Encrypted location record ID only. Precise coordinates stay inside wallet storage. |
+| Share purpose-bound access | `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/access-requests` plus 211-AI `#/recipient-access`, or direct `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/records/{record_id}/grants` | Active grant receipt with partner DID, purpose such as `housing_navigation_intake`, selected abilities, expiration or review date, and output caveats. |
+| Partner uses bounded access | 211-AI `#/recipient-access` or document-analysis API endpoints | Redacted derived artifact or summary only; raw contact details, identifiers, and document text are not present unless `record/decrypt` was explicitly granted. |
+| Prove eligibility | 211-AI `#/proof-center` or `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations/{location_record_id}/region-proofs` | `location_region` proof receipt with `is_simulated=false` in target staging and public inputs containing region claim data only. `lat`, `lon`, target coordinates, witnesses, and secrets must not appear. |
+| Contribute approved analytics | `POST /analytics/templates`, `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/analytics/consents/from-template`, `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/analytics/contributions`, and approved aggregate count endpoints | Approved template ID, consent ID, contribution proof/nullifier, allowed derived fields, released aggregate metadata, and privacy-budget entry. |
+| Revoke partner access | 211-AI `#/recipient-access`, `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/access-requests/{request_id}/revoke`, or `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/grants/{grant_id}/revoke` | Revoked receipt, blocked post-revocation invocation, and `revocation_propagation` health status not `error`. |
+| Audit workflow | 211-AI `#/audit` and `GET /wallets/{wallet_id}/audit` | Timeline includes `record/add`, `access/request`, `access/approve`, partner use, `proof/create`, `analytics/consent_create`, `analytics/contribute`, `analytics/query`, `access/revoke`, and `grant/revoke`. |
+
+The pilot is not ready if any evidence artifact contains plaintext document
+contents, precise coordinates, proof witnesses, bearer tokens, key material,
+secret-manager resolved values, or unapproved analytics fields. Keep
+`location_distance` hidden from live proof-center creation until its WALLET-180
+distance cutover packet is approved.
+
+The live browser rehearsal is
+`wallet_interface/ui/tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts`. The WALLET-210 case starts
+a real wallet API backed by local encrypted storage, uploads a document through
+the 211-AI UI, adds a wallet location through the API, approves partner access,
+runs partner redacted analysis, creates a deterministic non-simulated
+location-region proof, contributes to an approved analytics template, revokes
+access, verifies the partner is blocked, and checks the audit surface.
+
